This directory holds full, working reference solutions — one .py per challenge, named to
match the challenge directory (e.g. `01-word-frequency.py`).

They are here for ONE purpose: to check AFTER you have attempted a challenge yourself.

Reading the reference before attempting throws away the practice rep — the whole point is
that YOU write the body under interview-like constraints (see ../CONSTRAINTS.md). Attempt
first, run the tests, get stuck or get green, and only THEN diff your code against the
reference to learn what was cleaner.

(The file is named `.gitignore-note` rather than `.gitignore` on purpose — these solutions
ARE tracked in git so `verify.py --reference` can confirm every test tier is reachable. The
name is just a flag to your eyes: don't peek.)
